   Key Information
     * The following lists the supported platforms:
          + win32aloem - Windows 2000, XP
          + sunos5aloem - Solaris 8, 9, 10
          + linuxaloem - RedHat 7.2 and higher.
   ______________________________________________________________________

   User Interface Defects Repaired in 6.4d
     * Noise in the form of a 2 pixel high residual image will sometimes appear
       at  the top of the Wave and Structure windows. This issue has been
       resolved.
     * The wave zoomrange is no longer incorrectly reset by certain actions
       (such as adding a cursor) in the Wave window when Expanded Time is
       enabled.
     * The times for cursors in the Wave window (shown in the cursor pane) are
       now correct when Expanded Time is enabled. The value which indicates the
       time difference between two cursors now indicates the number of deltas
       or number of events (depending on which Expanded Time mode is selected)
       between the two cursors if the cursors are at the same simulation time.
     * Fixed a bug when a simulation is run for an additional amount after
       Expanded Time is enabled in the Wave window.
     * Fixed several problems with panning/scrolling/zooming when Expanded Time
       is enabled in the Wave window.
     * Fixed a crashing bug when enabling Expanded Time in a Wave window which
       contains certain types of signals (e.g. edited waveforms).
     * Message markers are now drawn at the correct time/location when Expanded
       Time is enabled in the Wave window.
     * "Expand  Packed Mem" and "Identify Memories Within Cells" were not
       functioning good through the GUI in terms of updating the memory list
       and their toggle state in menus.
     * Within a given VHDL architecture, if multiple blocks exist with the same
       name, objects declared within the blocks would get confused. This would
       result in incorrect results for the add log, add wave, add list, and
       examine commands.
     * Verilog process variables can now be logged.
     * ModelSim/Questasim crashed when trying to add a SystemVerilog static
       string array into Wave window or List window.
     * System Verilog inout typed enums didn't show any value in the wave
       window.
     * In Wave window, expanding any bus which has been assigned a color causes
       a crash of the simulator. This issue has been resolved.
     * Testplan Import in the Verification Manager failed if the directory or
       filename of the input or output files had spaces in them.
     * For   the   Wave  window,  the  Save  Image  dialog  accessed  via
       File->Export->Image... menu pick did not automatically add the .bmp
       extension when Files of type was set to "Bitmap (*.bmp)".
     * Wave window postscript printing does not work with some printers. This
       issue has been resolved.
     * Context-menu item "Save Files..." restored to "Files" pane... emits a
       sorted duplicate-free list of all the files used in the design (based on
       "write report").
     * Verilog reg bits and VHDL array elements where sometimes displayed
       incorrectly when the display was zoomed out.
     * The find insource command sometimes produces an internal Tcl error. This
       issue has been resolved.
     * Waveforms were sometimes drawn incorrectly (or not drawn at all) when
       using Expanded Time Deltas Mode or Expanded Time Events Mode if the
       simulation time at the right edge of the Wave window was a time that had
       no events. This has been fixed.
     * When  issuing  a  waveform  compare, where the 'gold' WLF file has
       assertions that does not exist in the 'test' WLF file, an incorrect
       failure with the following error could occur but now compares correctly.
       Fatal  WLF  Error (2): ../../../src/tkgui/compare.c(2639) Internal
       assertion: testRegion!=NULL
     * The noforce command failed when applied to a net whose name consisted of
       a  Verilog-format extended identifier, where the characters of the
       identifier terminated with a space-character. The command produced an
       error with the message, "No objects found".
     * When using a location map, the soft path was not correctly expanded if
       choosing the design unit and doing a recompile from the popup menu
       (Library Window Popup Menu > Recompile).
     * Fixed a crash related to waveform comparisons involving SC FIFO under
       certain circumstances.
     * Selecting a memory within the Memory window, and issuing the "Export
       data patterns" command would work properly the first time. A second
       attempt to issue this command on the same memory would result in an
       error. The issue has been corrected.
     * The preference "testtrackercolumnMap" saved in the .modelsim file to
       preserve the column order for the Verification Management Tracker window
       between sessions. Some operations resulted in the invalid value of "-1"
       being included in the list of column numbers saved for the value of that
       preference. This invalid value in turn caused tcl errors when using the
       Tracker window in older releases (prior to 6.4). This invalid value,
       "-1", will no longer be saved ! in the .modelsim file and will no longer
       cause tcl errors (in 6.3k and later) if it exists in a .modelsim file.
   ______________________________________________________________________

   Verilog Defects Repaired in 6.4d
     * The compiler produced an internal error in some cases when a module port
       was declared as a type defined in a package.
     * If a design with a nested configuration is optimized by vopt, then vsim
       is invoked on the optimized design, but with the -novopt switch, the
       simulator will incorrectly attempt to load the unoptimized version of
       the nested configuration, and will report the error message:
       "** Error: Could not find machine code for ..."
     * An out-of-bounds assignment to an array of reals resulted in a simulator
       crash in some cases.
     * Simple macros can be both defined and used within the context of another
       macro.
     * The simulator could crash with SystemVerilog designs where a wire in a
       package has the same dimensions as a register in a module. For example:
package g_pkg;
   wire [ 1 : 0 ] ww ;
endpackage

module g;
   import g_pkg::ww;
   reg  [ 1 : 0 ]  rrr;
endmodule
     * The simulator would crash when a clocking block used a concatenation
       containing a hierarchical bit select or slice.
     * A design optimized with +acc=n and +floatparameters resulted in a GUI
       crash  when  accessing  a vector net having a range dependent on a
       parameter.
     * In some cases, designs with false generate conditions would fail to
       elaborate if vopt was not used.
     * Functions  in  nested module were not being recognized as constant
       function. This has now been fixed.
     * A  constant  function inside a class when calling another constant
       function from an outer scope,was not recognized as a constant function.
       This has now been fixed.
     * Declaration a parameter or localparam with a complex value expression
       inside of a task or function would sometimes give an internal error
       like:
         ** Error: test.sv(12): Internal error:
       ../../../src/vlog/vgencode.c(129) vl_save_stack_on_wait
     * For unique case statement, invoking vopt with the option +acc=f would
       sometimes result in error such as:
       Internal error: ../../../src/vlog/vgenexpr.c(10724) !is_cancelledOf(e)
       This is now fixed.
     * A Verilog file was parsed as a SystemVerilog file when vlog was run with
       -mfcu and one of the files had something in $unit scope.
     * vlog  and  vopt  would  sometimes  report an internal error when a
       hierarchical reference was used to call first(), last(), next() and
       prev() on an associative array. The error message was:
       ** Error: bug.sv(14): Internal error: ../../../src/vlog/vgenexpr.c(7833)
       t
     * Some optimized sequential cells did not function correctly after a
       timingcheck violation. There outputs appeared to be stuck at X.
     * Slicing  an  array  of  interfaces  using parameters, For example,
       intf_inst[0 : p2] might have resulted in an "Unexpected signal: 11" in
       vlog or vopt. This has now been fixed.
     * vlog would crash when reading the Verilog source text "`pragma reset
       protect".
     * The  wrong delay path is selected when an unoptimized Verilog cell
       specifies delay path as (dataa *> dataout).
     * Assigning an unsized 'x' or 'z' to a register wider than 32-bits only
       set the low 32-bits.
     * When a module contains multiple UDP instances and the different UDP's
       are compiled in different libraries then for vopt mode, vsim sometimes
       produces the following error message:
       **     Error:     (vsim-3033)     top.v(7):    Instantiation    of
       '/test/bug/lib3.ut_udp2(verilog)' failed. The design unit was not found.
       This has been fixed.
     * vlog would fail to read a design while issuing the error:
       ... unexpected "end of source code".
     * Casting a parameter of string type to an integer type would sometimes
       produce a crash or give wrong results. This is now fixed.
     * A continuous assignment having a variable driver delay behaved as if
       there was no delay in some cases if the assignment was from one vector
       net to another of equal width.
     * Under certain circumstances (e.g. a method in a parameterized class, a
       forward typedef), vlog would print an invalid error about a field of a
       struct not being found.
     * Backslash characters would not be properly formatted within string
       literals in the output of vlog's -E option.
     * A non-wire connection to a module port net declared with a "net delay"
       simulated with zero delay in an optimized design if the module instance
       was inlined.
     * An always block triggered by a hierarchical reference (or a structure
       field  select)  failed  to  trigger  in some cases in an optimized
       SystemVerilog design.
     * An illegal assign to a void function name when the function is declared
       as extern caused a segmentation fault. This is now fixed.
     * In  order  to support SDF annotation of protected Verilog regions,
       $sdf_annotate calls that meet certain conditions are "hoisted" and
       treated as if they were specified on vsim command line. The conditions
       are that $sdf_annotate is either the first statement in a block or every
       statement  preceding  it  is a built-in systask. (We used to allow
       user-defined systasks too. Now restricted to built-in systasks only).
     * Continuous assignment to a wire from an untyped parameter might have
       resulted in a wrong value. This has now been fixed.
     * Assigning an interface-array formal port to a virtual interface could
       cause a runtime crash.
     * Verilog or SystemVerilog string parameter overrides from the command
       line(-G/-g) can now be specified without double-quoting the string. For
       example -Gstring_param=Hello.
     * Using  the +initreg=u switch to initialize UDP registers may cause
       incorrect simulation results.
     * NaN  results  from  a divide-by-zero operation in a variable delay
       expression is not detected and properly reported.
     * vlog printed an internal error when a continuous assignment used a
       concatenation of individual bits of an enum variable.
     * The  vsim  command line option +notimingchecks may cause incorrect
       simulation result in an optimized sequential cell that models negative
       timing checks.
     * Simultaneous events did not always violate $hold and $recovery timing
       checks.
     * Timing checks disabled with limits set to zero were not being used to
       solve delay net delays required by negative timing check limits.
     * Fixed a $system() issues that only existed on Windows.
     * An event control having either a posedge or negedge on a part-select of
       a vector register incorrectly triggered when the edge occurred on bits
       other than the LSB of the part-select.
     * If a replication operation with a zero replication multiplier appears
       inside a concatenation, it will be considered to be of size zero and
       ignored.
     * An always block that assigned to a variable with a blocking assignment
       incorrectly re-queued the same always block for execution in some cases
       if the variable also appeared in the sensitivity list of the event
       control. While an always block is running, none of its event controls
       should be considered active.
   ______________________________________________________________________

   PLI Defects Repaired in 6.4d
     * This release fixes some problems with the bits derived by VPI iteration
       on some classes of nets and ports.
     * Some learn mode defects have been fixed. One defect caused the simulator
       to crash when the VPI application used the vpi_put_value() function
       under certain conditions. Another defect caused the simulator to crash
       for some SignalSpy usages.
     * PLI/FLI shared objects that register exit callbacks using g_atexit()
       would sometime crash the simulator during quit. This is fixed now.
     * The  vpiScope  and  vpiModule transitions from VPI objects of type
       vpiGenScope are now available.
     * Some issues getting VPI objects that are subcomponents of complex mixed
       unpacked/packed structs using vpi_handle_by_name() have been fixed.
     * VPI assertion callback was not working correctly when assertion property
       was disabled by disable_iff construct. This has now been fixed.
   ______________________________________________________________________

   VHDL Defects Repaired in 6.4d
     * Complex  expressions  in  the  binding  indications of a component
       configuration could be incorrectly optimized.
     * The simulator could crash when elaborating a design with a subtype local
       to a function and in which the subtype refers to array attributes of the
       return value of that function.
     * In some cases when VHDL blocks had generic maps with generic dependent
       port  ranges and were used inside generates, a port mismatch error
       occurs. This is now fixed
     * Some error conditions were not detected when a force command was applied
       to a subelement of a composite port of mode in or inout. Error number
       3456 is now correctly issued in these cases.
     * The simulator crashed when attempting to load a black box design with an
       optimized VHDL top-level design unit.
   ______________________________________________________________________

   FLI Defects Repaired in 6.4d
     * mti_GetSignalSubelements would incorrectly report an error if the signal
       argument was a signal that did not contain any scalar signals. A signal
       will not contain any scalar signals if it is an array of length 0 (NULL
       array) or is record with no fields or all the fields are NULL arrays.
   ______________________________________________________________________

   VITAL Defects Repaired in 6.4d
     * In VITAL memory models, some HOLD violations were incorrectly reported
       as SETUP violations, and some HOLD violations reported an incorrect
       state (High vs. Low). This issue has been resolved.
   ______________________________________________________________________

   SystemC Defects Repaired in 6.4d
     * Added support for the SystemVerilog disable statement that involves
       DPI-SC calls.
   ______________________________________________________________________

   Assertion Defects Repaired in 6.4d
     * vsim crashed when using boolean repeats with repeat count greater than
       10000.
     * vlog gave parsing error for valid embedded PSL code present in a module
       compiled with -v switch but not being used in the design.
     * Forward referencing in now supported in PSL.
     * vlog gave error when concatenation operator '{var}' was used in PSL
       built-in functions.
     * Use of unclocked PSL built-in in abort expression caused vlog to give
       internal error.
     * The HTML report was not showing the Assertions Summary consistently with
       the command vcover stats (the HTML report was only showing assertion
       successes). Now it is consistent with vcover stats, and shows Assertion
       Passes and Assertion Failures.
   ______________________________________________________________________

   Mixed Language Defects Repaired in 6.4d
     * Using  SignalSpy  to mirror the value of single-bit vectors at the
       SystemVerilog-VHDL boundary, e.g. VHDL std_logic_vector(4 to 4) to
       Verilog reg [0:0], would produce an incorrect type mismatch error. This
       has been fixed.
   ______________________________________________________________________

   Coverage Defects Repaired in 6.4d
     * Applying statement exclusions to entire source files used to ignore the
       -item argument. This is fixed now.
     * Fixed a bug regarding exclusion report for "case" branches.
     * A problem with clearing "case" branch bins exclusion in coverage view
       mode has been fixed.
     * Fixed the possibility of a vsim crash when code coverage is on and a
       SystemVerilog generate block contains an instance which is inlined. For
       the  moment  we are inhibiting inlining of the instance within the
       generate block. A full repair will not be possible in the 6.4x release
       sequence, but will be included in a later release.
     * The GUI incorrectly highlighted portions of text when multiple Verilog
       statements were found on a single line of source.
     * HTML coverage reports can now be generated for the simulation dataset.
     * The "View Coverage Details" item of popup menu in the Verification
       Management Tracker window is now disabled (grayed out) when the row
       selected has a type which has no coverage details.
     * Excluded toggles incorrectly show up in HTML coverage reports. This is
       fixed.
     * The  HTML summary report now shows the count of passing tests with
       warnings separately.
     * Wrong toggle coverage statistics shown in Workspace window in simulation
       mode when some bits of a vector are excluded.
     * The Missed Coverage window did not show the last "elsif" missed branch
       when "else" was absent in the branch.
     * A Missed expression was showing as a missed condition in viewcov mode
       when only FEC of the expression was missed.
     * Merge produced incorrect toggle 0->Z transition counts.
     * VHDL process statements were not getting included in statement coverage.
       This was inconsistent with Verilog where we included always statements
       in statement coverage. Now VHDL process statements will appear in code
       coverage.
     * Sometimes  when  compiling a design unit with -cover bcesft, which
       instantiates a design unit compiled with -cover bcesfx, the following
       erroneous error would occur:
       ** Error: (vcom-1913) Ambiguous options bcesfx, toggle and extended
       toggle both specified.
       This has been fixed.
     * There are two different coverage flows:
        The Manual Flow that includes toggle add/disable/enable.
        The Compile/Simulator Flow that includes vsim coverage with coverage
            exclude.
       Fixed a problem when using the toggle add command from the first flow
       and then excluding nodes using the coverage exclude command from the
       second flow.
   ______________________________________________________________________

   General Defects Repaired in 6.4d
     * The string "(null)" appears in the transcript when some SignalSpy errors
       are suppressed. This issue has been resolved.
     * vcover could crash when merging UCDB files for certain VHDL designs.
       This has been corrected.
     * Attempting to add wave, list or log a VlTypedef would cause a crash.
     * The Verilog API method for transaction recording, $begin_transaction(),
       failed to handle its "begin_time" parameter correctly. The parameter was
       treated as if it were a 32-bit integer time. This has been corrected.
     * For the -vcdstim feature, ascending order buses (i.e. 0 to 31) could
       sometimes be reversed in the resulting vcdstim simulation.
     * Using checkpoint/restore with designs that use the built-in OVM library
       crash on restore or restart. This issue has been resolved.
     * In some cases under OVM, transaction streams were mis-named with the
       string    passed    as    the    "stream    kind"   parameter   to
       $create_transaction_stream(). This has been corrected.
     * The vmake utility generates combined make rules for Verilog design units
       when the source files are compiled with the same command line arguments.
       In some cases, the vlog command for the combined rule did not list all
       the source files.
     * Batch mode execution of dofiles containing add wave commands could fail
       to be replaced with the equivalent log commands. This has been fixed.
     * When a library containing an optimized "black box" (bbox) design is
       moved to a new location, incorrect "file not found" errors were reported
       when a fatal error occurred.
     * -gen_xml will function normally when the library and/or module files are
       read-only.
     * When  using -mixedansiports, vlog continues to generate a warning.
       Changed  the  handling  (for  -mixed cases ONLY) so the warning is
       suppressible by the customer.
     * Fixed problems with UCDB TESTSTATUS in simulation mode.
     * Added exclusion information to the XML report.
     * Fixed problems with Generated HTML report and altered it to be more like
       GUI/tracker.
     * Fixed UCDB coverage save hang.
   ______________________________________________________________________

   Mentor Graphics DRs Repaired in 6.4d
     * dts0100254528 - Wave window displays misleading information.
     * dts0100258656  - Wave window does not shows all events on a bus on
       Solaris.
     * dts0100514324 - Invalid warning: WLF and DBG files do not appear to be
       from the same design.
     * dts0100514601 - Problem logging signals to sub-groups with same name in
       Wave window.
     * dts0100519187 - If grouped signals are cut with CTRL-X they cannot be
       inserted again.
     * dts0100522177 - Some error conditions were not detected when a force
       command was applied to a subelement of a composite port of mode in or
       inout.
     * dts0100529195  - Long paths hide messages like "Limited Visibility
       region". Messages must be right-justified.
     * dts0100535601 - Simulation crash when coverage is enabled while loading
       an optimized design.
     * dts0100542918 - Invalid error for Field/method name (xxx) not in 'yyy'.
     * dts0100543642 - Signal information in the Wave window disappears when
       zooming.
     * dts0100544421 - Inside operator with logic variables return wrong values
       when the range of variables is smaller than the range of values in the
       'inside' operator'.
     * dts0100544621 - "Save List..." menu function reports with strange text
       format.
     * dts0100544838 - Expanded Time: Waveforms drawn incorrectly in Deltas
       Mode.
     * dts0100545180 - Crash when assigning color to wave in Wave window.
     * dts0100546033  -  Crash when the user browses the hierarchy in the
       workspace.
     * dts0100546372 - vlog crashes when using a parameter to slice an array of
       interfaces.
     * dts0100547150 - vlog assertion failure with parameter in a task.
     * dts0100548148 - Complex expressions in the binding indications of a
       component configuration could be incorrectly optimized.
     * dts0100550185  -  Some optimized sequential cells did not function
       correctly after a timing check violation. There outputs appeared to be
       stuck at X.
     * dts0100550304 - Numerical overflow error in $begin_transaction().
     * dts0100550403 - vlog and vopt would sometimes report an internal error
       when a hierarchical reference was used to call first(), last(), next()
       and prev() on an associative array.
     * dts0100551190 - Assigning an unsized 'x' or 'z' to a register wider than
