     * dts0100551191 - Simulator hangs during coverage save.
     * dts0100551483 - Verilog configuration doesn't choose the right SDF when
       using bbox flow.
     * dts0100552883 - Difference in simulation results between accelerated
       vital and -novital.
     * dts0100552888 - Bad return type from SystemVerilog Interface function
       created under VHDL.
     * dts0100559494 - Wrong behavior in assign statement when time delay is a
       variable.
     * dts0100559840 - vlog reports unexpected EOF while reading include file.
     * dts0100560539 - Simulation crashes with Exit Code 211 when trying to
       restore on a checkpoint using a OVM design.
     * dts0100560834 - Changes to the UCDB TESTSTATUS flag are ignored by
       coverage save.
     * dts0100561163  -  The  find insource command generates error in PA
       simulation.
     * dts0100561463 - Variables in Location Maps are not used correctly when
       recompiling.
     * dts0100561477 - Incorrect simulation result when vopt is enabled in 64c.
     * dts0100562206 - Simulation differs when optimized with code coverage
       enabled.
     * dts0100562213 - $system("terminal command line") doesn't work in windows
       but works in UNIX.
     * dts0100562523 - Waveform compare crash.
     * dts0100562669  - The problem is that $sdf_annotate is not executed
       sequentially inside an initial block.
     * dts0100562786 - Noforce does not handle escaped identifiers correctly.
     * dts0100566059 - vcover reports for toggle coverage differ based on UCDB
       file order during merge.
     * dts0100566743 - Testplan coverage summary discrepancy.
     * dts0100566865 - Strange transaction streams displayed in Wave window.
     * dts0100543980 - The GUI setting Identify Memories Within Cells does not
       work.
     * dts0100563015 - Fatal SIGSEGV in 6.4c when trying to pass an array of
       interfaces to a program block.
     * dts0100562203 - Cannot pass in string parameter via the command line.
     * dts0100562526 - Error when trying to access individual bits of an enum
       in an assign statement.
     * dts0100540661 - Excluded toggles appear in HTML coverage report.
     * dts0100563396 - vmake problem with 2 source files.
     * dts0100508495  -  "add wave" and "log" should not accept different
       parameters.
     * dts0100543545 - XML report displays coverage data for conditional rows
       that were coverage excluded.
     * dts0100552901 - Assertion data not showing up in vcover report -html.
     * dts0100476539 - GUI crashes with Font treeFont still in cache message.
